dialogue with three index cards.

@endnode


@node "Index Card 'General'" "Using zView"
@toc "Preferences Dialogue"
@{U}2.9.1 Index Card 'General'                                       zView@{u}

When the @{"preferences dialogue" LINK "Preferences Dialogue"} is displayed, you will see the index
card 'General' first.


@limage "images/cardgeneral.bmp" 0


In this index card, you can configure some general settings.

With the checkboxes @{B}Show read progress bar@{b} and @{B}Show write progress
bar@{b}, you can switch off the growing bar showing the progress of the
read or write process taking some time to execute. On low-end
computers, this speeds up displaying pictures a little bit.

@endnode


@node "Index Card 'Browser'" "Using zView"
@toc "Preferences Dialogue"
@{U}2.9.2  Index Card 'Browser'                                      zView@{u}

The second index card 'Browser' of the @{"preferences dialogue" LINK "Preferences Dialogue"}, in
particular, affect the display of the @{"directory list" LINK "Directory List"} and the @{"contents" LINK "Contents List"}
@{"list" LINK "Contents List"} of the @{"browser window" LINK "Browser Window"}.


@limage "images/cardbrowser.bmp" 0


You can alter the following settings:

 ù For @{B}Show file size@{b}, the size of a file will be displayed below
   the filename in the @{"contents list" LINK "Contents List"}.

 ù When the checkbox @{B}Show hidden files@{b} is active, hidden files and
   folders @{"[3]" LINK "[3]"} are shown in the @{"contents list" LINK "Contents List"}.

   With the information box of your desktop (for example, with jinnee
   or Thing), you can modify file attributes. If the hidden attribute
   of a file is set, generally, the file is not shown in the drive
   contents window of your desktop, in the file selection dialogue
   and so on.

 ù With @{B}Show unsupported files@{b} active, in addition to folders,
   picture/animation files (or thumbnails respectively) and PDF
   files, other files are displayed in the @{"contents list" LINK "Contents List"}, too; in
   other words, files which cannot be viewed by zView are also shown
   in the @{"contents list" LINK "Contents List"}.

   Please pay attention that the menu entry View/Show Only Images is
   not ticked. If so, regardless the 'Show unsupported files' option,
   only @{"zView-compatible picture and animation files" LINK "Supported File Formats"} are listed.

 ù With the popup button @{B}Smooth Thumbnails@{b}, you can select a
   computation method to smooth thumbnails. This is very slow and
   only available in @{"true-colour" LINK "Colour Depth"} (24 and 32 bits) or near true-colour
   (16 bits, also called @{"high-colour" LINK "Colour Depth"}) display modes, but the results
   are perfect, specially with the Lanczos computation.

 ù In the @{B}Skip Drive@{b} section, you can choose which drives are not
   shown in the @{"directory list" LINK "Directory List"} (skipped drives are displayed in
   inverse video). This is useful for slow drives and/or drives with
   removable media (like floppy drives, Iomega Zip drives, CD-ROMs)
   and the pseudo-drive U: to speed up opening the @{"browser window" LINK "Browser Window"}.
   After a change, a restart is needed, that is to say, the @{"browser" LINK "Browser Window"}
   @{"window" LINK "Browser Window"} have to be closed and opened.

@endnode


@node "Index Card 'PDF'" "Using zView"
@toc "Preferences Dialogue"
@{U}2.9.3  Index Card 'PDF'                                          zView@{u}

The third and last index card of the @{"preferences dialogue" LINK "Preferences Dialogue"} affect the
display of PDF pages in the @{"PDF window" LINK "PDF Window"}.


@limage "images/cardpdf.bmp" 0


Please note, if you have changed the settings in this index card,
then they only apply to @{"PDF windows" LINK "PDF Window"} which will be opened after
confirming the @{"preferences dialogue" LINK "Preferences Dialogue"}.

You can change the following settings:

 ù When the checkbox @{B}Antialias fonts@{b} is active, an Atari-specific
   font rendering is used. On the one hand, this improves the text
   display a lot, but, on the other hand, it slows down the display
   speed of a PDF page.

 ù For @{B}Fit PDF to the window@{b}, the size of a PDF page will always be
   adapted in such a way that it can completely displayed in the PDF
   window.

@endnode


