@node "Edit/Delete" "zView's Menus"
@toc "The 'Edit' Menu"
@{U}3.3.5  Edit/Delete                                               zView@{u}

Shortcut: <Delete>

This menu entry deletes files and folders selected in the @{"contents" LINK "Contents List"}
@{"list" LINK "Contents List"} (use <Shift> to select more than one file/folder). By selecting
this entry, a dialogue will appear and you will be asked if you want
to delete the selected file(s).

Note that write-protected files and folders will also be deleted.
zView makes write-protected files/folders writable so that they can
be deleted without asking permission for it. This way, you will not
get those annyoing warnings that a file or folder cannot be deleted.

@endnode


