@node "View/Sort by Name" "zView's Menus"
@toc "The 'View' Menu"
@{U}3.4.1  View/Sort by Name                                         zView@{u}

Shows files in the @{"contents list" LINK "Contents List"} sorted alphabetically by name.

Please note that folders always appear sorted by name and are always
shown before files.

All the entries in this portion of the menu have a tick in front of
them when active, and they are alternatives (selecting one
deactivates the current setting).

@endnode


@node "View/Sort by Size" "zView's Menus"
@toc "The 'View' Menu"
@{U}3.4.2  View/Sort by Size                                         zView@{u}

This menu option shows files in the @{"contents list" LINK "Contents List"} sorted by their
size so that the longest file appears at the end of the list.

Please note that folders always appear sorted by name and are always
shown before files.

All the entries in this portion of the menu have a tick in front of
them when active, and they are alternatives (selecting one
deactivates the current setting).

@endnode


@node "View/Sort by Date" "zView's Menus"
@toc "The 'View' Menu"
@{U}3.4.3  View/Sort by Date                                         zView@{u}

Shows files in the @{"contents list" LINK "Contents List"} sorted by the datestamp. The
'youngest' file is placed at the beginning. Files with the same
datestamp are sorted by their timestamps.

Please note that folders always appear sorted by name and are always
shown before files.

All the entries in this portion of the menu have a tick in front of
them when active, and they are alternatives (selecting one
deactivates the current setting).

@endnode


@node "View/Show Directory List" "zView's Menus"
@toc "The 'View' Menu"
@{U}3.4.4  View/Show Directory List                                  zView@{u}

With this menu entry, you can determine whether the @{"directory list" LINK "Directory List"} is
displayed. When this is deactivated (not ticked), the @{"contents list" LINK "Contents List"}
use the entire @{"browser window" LINK "Browser Window"} to show the contents of a directory.

@endnode


@node "View/Show Only Images" "zView's Menus"
@toc "The 'View' Menu"
@{U}3.4.5  View/Show Only Images                                     zView@{u}

With this menu entry, you can toggle on/off showing only @{"zView-" LINK "Supported File Formats"}
@{"compatible picture and animation files" LINK "Supported File Formats"} in the @{"contents list" LINK "Contents List"}.

If the menu entry is not ticked, folders and other files are also
listed. Folders are displayed, however, only if the option 'Show
unsupported files' (see Preferences Dialogue, subchapter @{"Index Card" LINK "Index Card 'Browser'"}
@{"'Browser'" LINK "Index Card 'Browser'"}) is not active.

@endnode


@node "View/4:3 Thumbnails" "zView's Menus"
@toc "The 'View' Menu"
@{U}3.4.6  View/4:3 Thumbnails                                       zView@{u}

With this menu entry, you can change the width/height ratio of the
area that icons or thumbnails take up in the @{"contents list" LINK "Contents List"} to 4:3.
The thumbnails will be scaled correspondingly.

Both entries in this portion of the menu have a tick in front of them
when active, and they are alternatives (selecting one deactivates the
current setting).

See Icon/Thumbnail Display Configuration for a more detailed
explanation.

@endnode


@node "View/3:4 Thumbnails" "zView's Menus"
