@node "V1.0 (3rd March 2013)" "History"
@toc "History"
@{U}C  V1.0 (3rd March 2013)                                         zView@{u}

News

 - The options 'Show Non-Images' (menu entry) and 'Show common files'
   (option in the @{"index card 'Browser'" LINK "Index Card 'Browser'"} of the @{"preferences dialogue" LINK "Preferences Dialogue"})
   were renamed to 'Show only Images' and 'Show unsupported files',
   and they have a different meaning now. 'Show unsupported files'
   differentiates now between displaying all kind of files and only
   folders and @{"zView-compatible files" LINK "Supported File Formats"} in the @{"contents list" LINK "Contents List"} of the
   browser. And enabling 'Show only Images' results in displaying
   only thumbnails, that means just @{"zView-compatible picture" LINK "Supported File Formats"} and
   animation files.
 - PDF zoom level is remembered if the option 'Fit PDF to the window'
   is not set.
 - Updated documentation by Sascha Uhlig.
 - Revised RSC file by Sascha Uhlig.


Bug fixes

 - MagiC and TOS compatibility (BETA8 introduced one nasty bug in that
   matter).
 - Fixed a crash when user clicked on the info icon while the main
   window was in background.
 - Umlauts in PDF navigation list (bookmarks).
 - Fixed a bug in the GEM (X)IMG plugin.
 - A hidden memory bug, apparently without noticeable effects, but
   better have it fixed :-)
 - Long-standing bugs in DSP/NF JPEG decoder fixed (no crash with
   memory protection, JPEG export is not corrupted with DSP/NF
   decoder).
 - The option 'Show hidden files' in the @{"index card 'Browser'" LINK "Index Card 'Browser'"} of the
   @{"preferences dialogue" LINK "Preferences Dialogue"} also works with Unix hidden files (prefixed
   with a dot).
 - Scaling in full screen mode did not work properly (images that
   take up the whole screen had a colourful line on the right or
   lower side).
 - Corrected the dimensions of the progress bars.
 - Fixed a bug in the PNG plugin.
 - Shortcut <Control>+<U> also works with @{"PDF windows" LINK "PDF Window"}.
 - Fixed strange closing window behaviour.
 - In the @{"contents list" LINK "Contents List"} of the @{"browser window" LINK "Browser Window"}, the first line of icon
   frames does not touch the frame of the toolbar.
 - AV protocol also accepts filenames with apostrophes.


Known bugs

 - Umlauts in filenames in the @{"contents list" LINK "Contents List"} of the browser and in
   extended information of a file (Exif or metadata), displayed in
   the @{"information dialogue" LINK "Information Dialogue"}, are not shown correctly.
 - Background of some GIF animations is not redrawn correctly.

@endnode


@node "BETA8 (1st November 2011)" "History"
@toc "History"
@{U}C  BETA8 (1st November 2011)                                     zView@{u}

News

 - First release after 6 years. Zorro seems to have left the Atari
   platform. Recompilation of zView and all @{"codecs" LINK "Codec"} against the latest
   libraries with the latest GCC 4 (compiled for 68020-60 + FPU).
   Therefore, you get better compatibility, less crashes and a higher
   speed.
 - The Xpdf code was upgraded to version 3.03 (2011-aug-15). Thanks
   to it, the latest Adobe Portable Document Format specifications
   are supported now (PDF 1.6 and PDF 1.7).
 - Mem.ldg is no longer needed. It has no real meaning for zView.
 - The application is FireBee-ready. MiKRO did some test builds for
   the guys of the Atari ColdFire Project (@{"ACP" LINK "FireBee"}), and it did run!
 - NFJPEG.prg and JPEGD.prg updated (maybe it helps, maybe not :-)


Bug fixes

 - Fixed some bugs in LDG and WinDom libraries to make zView work
   under FreeMiNT with memory protection.


Known bugs

 - On ARAnyM, with the DSP cookie installed, some strange problems
   appear when saving a JPEG (and there is a crash with the memory
   protection).

@endnode


@node "BETA7a (25th December 2005)" "History"
@toc "History"
@{U}C  BETA7a (25th December 2005)                                   zView@{u}

There is now a special version of zView compatible with the MagiC
operating system (see folder 'MagiC'). This is a version compiled
with the old GCC 2.95.3 because it seems that MagiC cannot launch the
C++ application compiled with GCC 3.x.

@endnode


@node "BETA7 (24th December 2005)" "History"
@toc "History"
@{U}C  BETA7 (24th December 2005)                                    zView@{u}

News

 - PDF:
    Huge quality improvement in the PDF font rendering (Atari-
     specific).
    Zoom function added.
    Code upgraded to Xpdf 3.01pl1 (2005-dec-01).
 - Complete @{"Exif specification" LINK "Exif"} 2.1 support (and most from 2.2) for
   JPEG images (now, you can see various useful information, like the
   model of your camera, when the picture was taken, or if the flash
   of your camera was fired or not).
 - Now, zView can extract the thumbnails embedded inside JPEG images
   created with a digital camera. This means that the thumbnail
   creation is 20 times faster if the JPEG was created with a camera.
 - New options in the @{"preferences dialogue" LINK "Preferences Dialogue"} added:
    Skip Drive (preventing the CD-ROM drive, for example, being
     shown in the @{"directory list" LINK "Directory List"} speeds up opening the @{"browser" LINK "Browser Window"}
     @{"window" LINK "Browser Window"}).
    Smooth Thumbnails: now, you can smooth the thumbnails with
     various methods. This is very slow and only available in @{"true-" LINK "Colour Depth"}
     @{"colour" LINK "Colour Depth"} or near @{"true-colour" LINK "Colour Depth"} display, but the results are perfect
     (specially with the Lanczos computation).
    PDF font antialiasing on/off.
    Fit the PDF to the window.
 - Utilisation of an embedded font to have the same look on any
   computer.
 - Animated interlaced @{"GIFs" LINK "GIF"} and @{"animated GIFs" LINK "GIF"} with transparency are
   now supported.
 - More zoom levels for the pictures (25, 50, 100, 150 and 200%;
   previously: 50, 100 and 200%).
 - More icons (function shortcuts) added to the toolbars.


Bug fixes

 - Many bug fixes in the PDF code (rotated PDF, problems with some
   fonts and so on).
 - Missing horizontal slider computation in the PDF and image window.
 - Little memory leak corrected in the multi-timer function.
 - A memory block was not freed in the file rename function.
 - Some redraw problems fixed (for example, PDF bookmarks).
 - Other little bug fixed.


Known bugs

 - On ARAnyM, with the DSP cookie installed, some strange problems
   appear when saving a JPEG.

@endnode


@node "BETA6 (7th August 2005)" "History"
@toc "History"
@{U}C  BETA6 (7th August 2005)                                       zView@{u}

News

 - For compatibility with the PDF code, zView is now under @{"GPL" LINK "General Public License (GPL)"}
   license.
 - Animation support added. The first format benefitting from that is
   GIF (space bar for pause/resume).
 - PDF read support (you will need a lot of memory to read a PDF).
 - Reservoir Gods' GodPaint read and write support.
 - Zoom available with the browser toolbar or <+> and <-> on the
   numerical keyboard.
 - Documentation and zView icon provided by Sascha Uhlig. Thanks to
   him!
 - French translation of the RSC by Cyril Lefebvre. Thanks to him!
 - Now, zView can save from an interlaced picture.
 - The scrolling in the @{"picture window" LINK "Picture Window"} and the redraw function are a
   little bit faster.
 - Custom font added for the @{"index card 'Exif'" LINK "Index Card 'Exif'"} of the @{"information" LINK "Information Dialogue"}
   @{"dialogue" LINK "Information Dialogue"} to see more lines.
 - VDI-Enhancer from the Behne brothers provided in the folder
   'Goodies'. Install it if you use the standard Atari VDI instead
   of, for example, NVDI or fVDI.
 - Other little changes, like <Control>+<U> (standard) to close the
   window instead of <Control>+<W>, menu bar deactivation when a
   picture is loaded, or 'Out of memory' warning in the full screen
   code.


Bug fixes

 - Unnecessary redraws of the menu bar when the window was being
   scrolled.
 - Double redraw of the @{"browser window" LINK "Browser Window"} when it was opened.
 - When you open a selected folder in the @{"contents list" LINK "Contents List"} and you go
   back again, the folder remains selected. The code was there, but
   it was wrong.
 - Static MFDB structures were fried in 'winimg' and the full screen
   code!
 - 1-@{"plane" LINK "Colour Depth"} pictures and icons were not correctly drawn in full screen
   mode and in the browser toolbar.
 - The progress bar was one pixel too wide and high.
 - Problem with 1-bit DEGAS pictures corrected.
 - Now, the background in full screen mode is always black.
 - In the GIF @{"codec" LINK "Codec"}, a crash occurred if textual information was
   greater than 255 lines.
 - Incorrect translation in the GUI (octets -> bytes, and so on).


Known bugs

 - On ARAnyM, with the DSP cookie installed, some strange problems
   appear when saving a JPEG.
 - Various @{"animated GIFs" LINK "GIF"} are badly rendered.
 - For some rare @{"PDFs" LINK "PDF"}, the fonts are outlined.
 - The decoding of @{"PDFs" LINK "PDF"} with big pictures inside is very slow (not
   really a bug, but this code must be rewritten).

@endnode


@node "BETA5 (20th February 2005)" "History"
@toc "History"
@{U}C  BETA5 (20th February 2005)                                    zView@{u}

News

 - Versions of the binaries and @{"codecs" LINK "Codec"} for 68020-60 systems, and
   68000 and 68020 systems without FPU available.
 - Full screen mode with automatic picture resize if the picture is
   bigger than the screen (shortcut <F10>).
 - Another cool feature: when a window is iconified, zView shows a
   thumbnail of the picture inside the iconified window.
 - With the latest ARAnyM from CVS, the JPEG pictures are decoded
   natively with the host CPU! (In order to use this feature, put
   NFJPEG.prg in your Auto folder before MiNT.) Many thanks to
   Patrice Mandin for his work on ARAnyM!
 - The DSP and the main JPEG @{"codec" LINK "Codec"} are merged in only one codec. If
   the Brainstorm cookie is detected and you do not have a 68060, the
   JPEG is decoded with the DSP, or else the CPU routine is used.
 - Support of DEGAS compressed added (PC1, PC2, PC3).
 - Other little changes, like recompilation of all @{"codecs" LINK "Codec"} with the
   latest GCC, the possibility to move the about box with XaAES or
   information about the license.


Bug fixes

 - Many problems with other operating systems than MiNT are
   corrected. For example, the plugins were not loaded if these were
   in the global folder (LDGPATH\@{"Codecs" LINK "Codec"}) under TOS and MagiC.
 - Problems with some DEGAS images fixed.
 - With the DSP, JPEG pictures no multiple of 16 were badly decoded.
 - In @{"planes" LINK "Colour Depth"} < 8 bits, the @{"toolbar icons" LINK "Toolbar Icons"} were not shown.
 - VDI EdDI check at the start.
 - zView saves the @{"browser window" LINK "Browser Window"} coordinates when you quit the
   application. Now, these coordinates are not saved if this window
   is iconified (in order to prevent bad @{"browser window" LINK "Browser Window"} coordinates
   on next relaunch).
 - Other little bug fixes, like problems with the menu bar handling
   or error messages not correct.

@endnode


